<concept id="concept_E8D43EB4494E41D2AB42D4A89396D1AB" xml:lang="en-us">
    <title>Working with Data Visualizations</title>
    <conbody>
        <section>
            <p>The user interface for monitoring your services and virtual machines integrates with Grafana, an open source application for visualizing large-scale monitoring data on metrics dashboards. <ph
                    conref="../../shared/product-name.xml#ProductNameTopic/Product_Abbr"
                    /> ships with preconfigured dashboards for <ph
                    conref="../../shared/product-name.xml#ProductNameTopic/Product_Abbr"
                /> and OpenStack operators. As an application operator, you can configure your own dashboard as required. </p>
            <p>Use <uicontrol>Monitoring > Overview</uicontrol> in OpenStack Horizon and one of the options at the top border of the <uicontrol>Overview</uicontrol> page to access the preconfigured metrics dashboards. Use them as the starting point for creating your own dashboard with the data you want to visualize.</p>
        </section>
